The paper deals with video analytics in multi-camera networks, specifically for vehicle tracking and re-identification. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of zero-shot learning (ZSL) and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the framework to adversarial conditions, which is relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
